          "front": "Hungry",
          "back": "tengo hambre",
          "grammarNote": "Spanish uses tener (to have) for hunger, thirst, and temperature: tengo hambre (I'm hungry), tengo sed (I'm thirsty), tengo frío/calor (I'm cold/hot). These are 'having' a feeling, not 'being' one."
